Veteran actor Kanayo O. Kanayo has made an emotional appeal to President Muhammadu Buhari on the occasion of his diamond jubilee. KOK, who clocked 60 on Tuesday, begged the President to set free the leader of proscribed Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB), Nnamdi Kanu. In the video, the thespian explained his appeal was solely personal to put a total wrap to his 60th birthday celebration and not something borne out of coercion or persuasion to speak on behalf of a group of persons.   2022 Headies: I deserve an award, says Portable     Police pick up Timaya over alleged hit & run accident     Kim Kardashian legally single from Kanye West   He said: “My dear President and father of the nation, Muhammadu Buhari (GCFR) Commander-in-Chief of Armed Forces of the Federal Republic of Nigeria. I hope this message meets you well, sir. “My name is Kanayo O. Kanayo. I’m an actor and a lawyer. And I hold a national honour of Member of the Order of the Federal Republic (MFR). “Sir, on the occasion of my 60th birthday, I want to make an appeal to you as a son and a patriotic citizen whose industry contributes meaningfully to the nation’s GDP.